      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALWAYSBGOOD (8) is a progressive gelding yet to miss a place in four starts including two wins. Impressive when cruising home two back at Penrith then raced three wide without cover but stuck on for second to handy filly at this circuit and distance last time. Draws wider but he is up to winning this with even luck. KRUSTY KRUNCH (2) comes off some good efforts in the Nutrien Classic Sales 3F series where she placed in the heats before a midfield finish in the Listed final. Draws to make an impact. TRIED AND TRUSTED (1) continue some solid form when runner-up again last start, beaten a nose at Penrith. Can be competitive from the inside barrier. ROYAL VINCENT (3) led to win at Penrith last week. Draws a couple of spots wider but can still be prominent.",
